verses.text: \w I|strong="H5704"\w* \w will|strong="H3068"\w* praise thee, \w O|strong="H3068"\w* \w Lord|strong="H3068"\w*, \w with|strong="H3068"\w* \w my|strong="H3068"\w* whole heart; \w in|strong="H3427"\w* \w the|strong="H5002"\w* council \w of|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H5002"\w* just: \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w in|strong="H3427"\w* \w the|strong="H5002"\w* congregation.

Great \w are|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* works \w of|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* \w Lord|strong="H3068"\w*: sought \w out|strong="H7971"\w* according \w to|strong="H3068"\w* all \w his|strong="H3068"\w* wills.

\w His|strong="H3117"\w* work \w is|strong="H3117"\w* praise \w and|strong="H3117"\w* magnificence: \w and|strong="H3117"\w* \w his|strong="H3117"\w* justice continueth \w for|strong="H3117"\w* ever \w and|strong="H3117"\w* ever.

\w He|strong="H3068"\w* hath \w made|strong="H7650"\w* \w a|strong="H5921"\w* remembrance \w of|strong="H3068"\w* \w his|strong="H5921"\w* wonderful \w works|strong="H5921"\w*, being \w a|strong="H5921"\w* merciful \w and|strong="H3068"\w* gracious \w Lord|strong="H3068"\w*:

\w He|strong="H3117"\w* hath given food \w to|strong="H5921"\w* \w them|strong="H5921"\w* \w that|strong="H3117"\w* fear \w him|strong="H5921"\w*. \w He|strong="H3117"\w* \w will|strong="H4428"\w* \w be|strong="H0136"\w* mindful \w for|strong="H5921"\w* ever \w of|strong="H4428"\w* \w his|strong="H5921"\w* covenant:

\w He|strong="H5921"\w* \w will|strong="H0776"\w* shew forth \w to|strong="H5921"\w* \w his|strong="H5921"\w* \w people|strong="H1471"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* power \w of|strong="H0776"\w* \w his|strong="H5921"\w* \w works|strong="H5921"\w*.

\w That|strong="H3651"\w* \w he|strong="H3651"\w* may give \w them|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* inheritance \w of|strong="H7218"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* Gentiles: \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w works|strong="H5921"\w* \w of|strong="H7218"\w* \w his|strong="H5921"\w* hands \w are|strong="H1870"\w* truth \w and|strong="H7218"\w* judgment.
All his commandments are faithful: confirmed for ever and ever, made in truth and equity.
He hath sent redemption to his people: he hath commanded his covenant for ever. Holy and terrible is his name:
The fear of the Lord is the beginning of wisdom. A good understanding to all that do it: his praise continueth for ever and ever.
